# FastAPI + Celery + MySQL Project Walkthrough

## Summary of Accomplishments

All requirements for the assignment have been successfully fulfilled. We have created a fully functional background processing system backed by FastAPI, MySQL, and Redis.

### 1. Database & Models
- Replaced SQLite with a robust `pymysql` MySQL connection using SQLAlchemy ([app/database.py](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/database.py)).
- Designed the [NewsArticle](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/models.py#5-21) schema ([app/models.py](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/models.py)) with proper indexing on `published_date`, `title`, and `url` to optimize searches by date.
- Dynamically created the `news_db` database and automatically generated tables upon running FastAPI.

### 2. FastAPI Endpoints & Timing Middleware
- Built the `GET /news` API endpoint ([app/main.py](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/main.py)) which searches the database by `published_date`.
- Created custom [add_process_time_header](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/main.py#23-68) middleware that intercepts the HTTP response, reconstructs the json body stream, and successfully injects ` total_time_taken ` into the final JSON payload.

### 3. Celery & Periodic Tasks
- Integrated Celery ([app/worker.py](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/worker.py)) using your local Redis server on Windows (WSL) as the message broker.
- Used `requests` to fetch Top Headlines from News API ([app/services/news_api.py](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/services/news_api.py)).
- Registered a Celery Beat crontab task (`fetch-news-every-minute`) that schedules the fetch automation.

### 4. Logging & Error Handling
- Provided a centralized custom logger component ([app/logger.py](file:///C:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/app/logger.py)) that outputs clean INFO, WARNING, and ERROR logs across FastAPI threads and background Celery processes.
- Handled empty API keys, network request timeouts, exception rollbacks in MySQL transactions, and malformed database reads with appropriate HTTP 500 exceptions and logging mechanisms.

---

## Validation & Results

The complete system has been verified locally.

**1. Celery Fetching Test:**
- **Action**: Ran the Celery worker and Celery beat process.
- **Result**: The worker connected to Redis and successfully received the scheduled task. We confirmed the insertion transaction in the log: `[INFO] Successfully stored 19 new articles.`

**2. API Responses and Timing Middleware Test:**
- **Action**: Queried `http://127.0.0.1:8000/news?date=2026-03-03`
- **Result**: 
  ```json
  {
      "data": [
          {
              "title": "Dow drops 1,200 points - CNBC live updates",
              "url": "https://www.cnbc.com...",
              "published_at": "2026-03-03T18:00:00Z"
          },
          ... 18 more items
      ],
      "total_time_taken": 8.83
  }
  ```
  The endpoint successfully fetched data from MySQL while measuring a processing time around `8.8ms`.

