## How to Run It Yourself

Currently, the server processes are running in the background. If you ever need to stop and restart them manually, open 3 different PowerShell windows and activate your virtual environment ([.\venv\Scripts\Activate](file:///c:/Users/Pratham%20Shetty/Desktop/Jarvis_Invest_Assignment/venv/Scripts/Activate)) in all of them:

1. **Terminal 1 (Start FastAPI)**:
   ```powershell
   uvicorn app.main:app --reload
   ```
2. **Terminal 2 (Start Celery Worker)**:
   ```powershell
   celery -A app.worker.celery_app worker -l INFO -P eventlet
   ```
3. **Terminal 3 (Start Celery Beat Scheduler)**:
   ```powershell
   celery -A app.worker.celery_app beat -l INFO
   ```

You can then test your APIs at `http://localhost:8000/docs` (Swagger UI).
